00:00:22.319 --> 00:00:26.159
Uniqul allows a user to buy things with their
face.

00:00:26.159 --> 00:00:31.089
The world's first facial recognition payment
system simply requires the customer to confirm

00:00:31.089 --> 00:00:34.250
their purchase by clicking okay on a tablet.

00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:39.230
The system recognizes your face and access
your information from its database and cuts

00:00:39.230 --> 00:00:43.110
down transaction time to less than 5 seconds.

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:47.820
They're preparing to test the system in Helsinki
and in case you're wondering about differentiating

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:51.640
identical twins they're going to need to enter
a pin password.

00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:57.000
The IH2 Azzurra Hand is the first robotic
hand on the market that is human-sized and

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.970
able to replicate real human hand functions
at human-like speeds.

00:01:01.970 --> 00:01:06.150
Created by Italian-based company Prensillia
- it can grasp different items at different

00:01:06.150 --> 00:01:11.659
weights with both power and precision grasps
as well as advanced digit manipulation and

00:01:11.659 --> 00:01:13.170
sensing abilities.

00:01:13.170 --> 00:01:18.780
And its uses range from prosthetics to humanoid
robotics and various research applications.

00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:23.280
Akira Miyawaki is creating forests to reduce
tsunami damage.

00:01:23.280 --> 00:01:29.700
The 1000 year Kibonooka project features dense
deep rooted trees planted in large mounds

00:01:29.700 --> 00:01:35.369
created by using debris from previous tsunami
destruction and locating these along the shores

00:01:35.369 --> 00:01:40.389
in Japan so that they can greatly reduce the
negative impact of future tsunamis by reducing

00:01:40.389 --> 00:01:42.960
the energy potential of the wave.

00:01:42.960 --> 00:01:47.229
This app lets you know in realtime which restaurants
have available seating.

00:01:47.229 --> 00:01:51.719
The system collects data throughout the dining
experience from seating and ordering to paying

00:01:51.719 --> 00:01:56.340
the bill by working with the restaurant's
point of sale system - giving real time exact

00:01:56.340 --> 00:02:01.359
updates depending on the actual situations
happening inside the restaurant - giving users

00:02:01.359 --> 00:02:05.950
in Japan the ability to choose a restaurant
based on seating availability.

